Integument:
Microtuberculate. Integument of notogaster and ventral plate with shallow foveae (Figs. 
3, 4
), that of prodorsum without foveae. Cerotegument microtuberculate, primarily present at dorsosejugal scissure and laterally on prodorsum (Fig. 
8
).

