Legs: Monodactylous. Seta d coupled with solenidion and present to tritonymph on genua I to III and tibiae I to IV in all immatures (
Table 1
). Shape of genual solenidion σ short, baculiform and subequal in length to seta d in immatures. Tibial solenidion φ 2 almost as long as seta d in deutonymph and tritonymph. Porose areas developed on femora I to IV and trochanters III and IV in the tritonymph, not evident in larva to deutonymph.

